{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":180,"text":"I have a confession to make."},{"time":1519,"text":"I'm a business professor"},{"time":3309,"text":"whose ambition has been\nto help people learn to lead."},{"time":5839,"text":"But recently, I've discovered"},{"time":7280,"text":"that what many of us\nthink of as great leadership"},{"time":10239,"text":"does not work when it comes\nto leading innovation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13519,"text":"I'm an ethnographer."},{"time":14920,"text":"I use the methods of anthropology"},{"time":16640,"text":"to understand the questions\nin which I'm interested."},{"time":19220,"text":"So along with three co-conspirators,"},{"time":21380,"text":"I spent nearly a decade observing\nup close and personal"},{"time":25200,"text":"exceptional leaders of innovation."},{"time":27679,"text":"We studied 16 men and women,"},{"time":29880,"text":"located in seven countries\nacross the globe,"},{"time":32439,"text":"working in 12 different industries."},{"time":34920,"text":"In total, we spent hundreds\nof hours on the ground,"},{"time":37920,"text":"on-site, watching these leaders in action."},{"time":41200,"text":"We ended up with pages and pages\nand pages of field notes"},{"time":44559,"text":"that we analyzed and looked\nfor patterns in what our leaders did."},{"time":47920,"text":"The bottom line?"},{"time":49979,"text":"If we want to build organizations\nthat can innovate time and again,"},{"time":53140,"text":"we must unlearn our conventional\nnotions of leadership."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56959,"text":"Leading innovation is not\nabout creating a vision,"},{"time":59560,"text":"and inspiring others to execute it."},{"time":62760,"text":"But what do we mean by innovation?"},{"time":64718,"text":"An innovation is anything\nthat is both new and useful."},{"time":68079,"text":"It can be a product or service."},{"time":69840,"text":"It can be a process\nor a way of organizing."},{"time":72519,"text":"It can be incremental,\nor it can be breakthrough."},{"time":75359,"text":"We have a pretty inclusive definition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77280,"text":"How many of you recognize this man?"},{"time":79879,"text":"Put your hands up."},{"time":82560,"text":"Keep your hands up,\nif you know who this is."},{"time":90319,"text":"How about these familiar faces?"},{"time":92599,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":94680,"text":"From your show of hands,"},{"time":95840,"text":"it looks like many of you\nhave seen a Pixar movie,"},{"time":98280,"text":"but very few of you recognized Ed Catmull,"},{"time":101239,"text":"the founder and CEO of Pixar --"},{"time":103879,"text":"one of the companies\nI had the privilege of studying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106799,"text":"My first visit to Pixar was in 2005,"},{"time":109479,"text":"when they were working on \"Ratatouille,\""},{"time":111400,"text":"that provocative movie about\na rat becoming a master chef."},{"time":114520,"text":"Computer-generated movies\nare really mainstream today,"},{"time":118439,"text":"but it took Ed and his\ncolleagues nearly 20 years"},{"time":121120,"text":"to create the first\nfull-length C.G. movie."},{"time":124960,"text":"In the 20 years hence,\nthey've produced 14 movies."},{"time":128240,"text":"I was recently at Pixar,\nand I'm here to tell you"},{"time":131000,"text":"that number 15 is sure to be a winner."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134069,"text":"When many of us think\nabout innovation, though,"},{"time":136280,"text":"we think about an Einstein\nhaving an 'Aha!' moment."},{"time":139919,"text":"But we all know that's a myth."},{"time":142280,"text":"Innovation is not about solo genius,"},{"time":145240,"text":"it's about collective genius."},{"time":148479,"text":"Let's think for a minute about\nwhat it takes to make a Pixar movie:"},{"time":152159,"text":"No solo genius, no flash of inspiration\nproduces one of those movies."},{"time":157680,"text":"On the contrary, it takes about\n250 people four to five years,"},{"time":162080,"text":"to make one of those movies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163639,"text":"To help us understand the process,"},{"time":166319,"text":"an individual in the studio\ndrew a version of this picture."},{"time":169960,"text":"He did so reluctantly,"},{"time":171469,"text":"because it suggested that the process \nwas a neat series of steps"},{"time":175840,"text":"done by discrete groups."},{"time":178130,"text":"Even with all those arrows,\nhe thought it failed to really tell you"},{"time":181990,"text":"just how iterative, interrelated\nand, frankly, messy their process was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186840,"text":"Throughout the making of a movie\nat Pixar, the story evolves."},{"time":192940,"text":"So think about it."},{"time":194520,"text":"Some shots go through quickly."},{"time":197280,"text":"They don't all go through in order."},{"time":199560,"text":"It depends on how vexing\nthe challenges are"},{"time":202199,"text":"that they come up with when they\nare working on a particular scene."},{"time":206520,"text":"So if you think about that scene in \"Up\""},{"time":208919,"text":"where the boy hands the piece\nof chocolate to the bird,"},{"time":212120,"text":"that 10 seconds took one animator\nalmost six months to perfect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218259,"text":"The other thing about a Pixar movie"},{"time":220000,"text":"is that no part of the movie\nis considered finished"},{"time":222400,"text":"until the entire movie wraps."},{"time":224319,"text":"Partway through one production,\nan animator drew a character"},{"time":228759,"text":"with an arched eyebrow that\nsuggested a mischievous side."},{"time":232760,"text":"When the director saw that\ndrawing, he thought it was great."},{"time":235770,"text":"It was beautiful, but he said,"},{"time":237199,"text":"\"You've got to lose it;\nit doesn't fit the character.\""},{"time":240020,"text":"Two weeks later, the director\ncame back and said,"},{"time":242480,"text":"\"Let's put in those few seconds of film.\""},{"time":244560,"text":"Because that animator\nwas allowed to share"},{"time":247600,"text":"what we referred to\nas his slice of genius,"},{"time":250800,"text":"he was able to help that director\nreconceive the character"},{"time":254120,"text":"in a subtle but important way\nthat really improved the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258759,"text":"What we know is, at the heart\nof innovation is a paradox."},{"time":263399,"text":"You have to unleash the talents\nand passions of many people"},{"time":267079,"text":"and you have to harness them\ninto a work that is actually useful."},{"time":271809,"text":"Innovation is a journey."},{"time":274049,"text":"It's a type of collaborative\nproblem solving,"},{"time":276879,"text":"usually among people\nwho have different expertise"},{"time":279639,"text":"and different points of view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281759,"text":"Innovations rarely get created full-blown."},{"time":284319,"text":"As many of you know,"},{"time":286449,"text":"they're the result,\nusually, of trial and error."},{"time":289199,"text":"Lots of false starts,\nmissteps and mistakes."},{"time":293399,"text":"Innovative work can be\nvery exhilarating,"},{"time":296199,"text":"but it also can be\nreally downright scary."},{"time":301730,"text":"So when we look at why it is\nthat Pixar is able to do what it does,"},{"time":307079,"text":"we have to ask ourselves,\nwhat's going on here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311839,"text":"For sure, history\nand certainly Hollywood,"},{"time":314800,"text":"is full of star-studded teams\nthat have failed."},{"time":317930,"text":"Most of those failures are attributed"},{"time":319790,"text":"to too many stars or too many\ncooks, if you will, in the kitchen."},{"time":324879,"text":"So why is it that Pixar,\nwith all of its cooks,"},{"time":328519,"text":"is able to be so successful\ntime and time again?"},{"time":333360,"text":"When we studied\nan Islamic Bank in Dubai,"},{"time":336439,"text":"or a luxury brand in Korea,\nor a social enterprise in Africa,"},{"time":341000,"text":"we found that innovative organizations"},{"time":343079,"text":"are communities that\nhave three capabilities:"},{"time":345879,"text":"creative abrasion, creative\nagility and creative resolution."},{"time":350959,"text":"Creative abrasion is about being able\nto create a marketplace of ideas"},{"time":355960,"text":"through debate and discourse."},{"time":358160,"text":"In innovative organizations,\nthey amplify differences,"},{"time":361079,"text":"they don't minimize them."},{"time":362319,"text":"Creative abrasion is not\nabout brainstorming,"},{"time":365360,"text":"where people suspend their judgment."},{"time":367480,"text":"No, they know how to have very\nheated but constructive arguments"},{"time":371439,"text":"to create a portfolio of alternatives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374600,"text":"Individuals in innovative organizations"},{"time":376879,"text":"learn how to inquire, they learn how\nto actively listen, but guess what?"},{"time":381169,"text":"They also learn how to\nadvocate for their point of view."},{"time":383959,"text":"They understand that\ninnovation rarely happens"},{"time":387879,"text":"unless you have both\ndiversity and conflict."},{"time":391960,"text":"Creative agility is about being able\nto test and refine that portfolio of ideas"},{"time":396760,"text":"through quick pursuit,\nreflection and adjustment."},{"time":400120,"text":"It's about discovery-driven learning"},{"time":401959,"text":"where you act, as opposed to plan,\nyour way to the future."},{"time":405199,"text":"It's about design thinking where\nyou have that interesting combination"},{"time":408680,"text":"of the scientific method\nand the artistic process."},{"time":412399,"text":"It's about running a series of\nexperiments, and not a series of pilots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416879,"text":"Experiments are usually about learning."},{"time":418760,"text":"When you get a negative outcome,"},{"time":420310,"text":"you're still really learning something\nthat you need to know."},{"time":423472,"text":"Pilots are often about being right."},{"time":425959,"text":"When they don't work,\nsomeone or something is to blame."},{"time":430319,"text":"The final capability\nis creative resolution."},{"time":433279,"text":"This is about doing decision making"},{"time":434990,"text":"in a way that you can actually combine\neven opposing ideas"},{"time":438519,"text":"to reconfigure them in new combinations"},{"time":441040,"text":"to produce a solution\nthat is new and useful."},{"time":444319,"text":"When you look at innovative organizations,\nthey never go along to get along."},{"time":448120,"text":"They don't compromise."},{"time":450199,"text":"They don't let one group\nor one individual dominate,"},{"time":453639,"text":"even if it's the boss,\neven if it's the expert."},{"time":458000,"text":"Instead, they have developed"},{"time":459839,"text":"a rather patient and more inclusive\ndecision making process"},{"time":463399,"text":"that allows for both/and\nsolutions to arise"},{"time":467079,"text":"and not simply either/or solutions."},{"time":469879,"text":"These three capabilities are why we see"},{"time":473879,"text":"that Pixar is able to do what it does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":478240,"text":"Let me give you another example,"},{"time":480209,"text":"and that example is the\ninfrastructure group of Google."},{"time":482839,"text":"The infrastructure group\nof Google is the group"},{"time":485519,"text":"that has to keep the website\nup and running 24/7."},{"time":489569,"text":"So when Google was about\nto introduce Gmail and YouTube,"},{"time":493439,"text":"they knew that their data storage\nsystem wasn't adequate."},{"time":496759,"text":"The head of the engineering group\nand the infrastructure group at that time"},{"time":500919,"text":"was a man named Bill Coughran."},{"time":503480,"text":"Bill and his leadership team,\nwho he referred to as his brain trust,"},{"time":507240,"text":"had to figure out what to do\nabout this situation."},{"time":511120,"text":"They thought about it for a while."},{"time":512960,"text":"Instead of creating a group\nto tackle this task,"},{"time":516440,"text":"they decided to allow groups\nto emerge spontaneously"},{"time":520720,"text":"around different alternatives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522159,"text":"Two groups coalesced."},{"time":525000,"text":"One became known as Big Table,"},{"time":528159,"text":"the other became known\nas Build It From Scratch."},{"time":531679,"text":"Big Table proposed that they\nbuild on the current system."},{"time":534600,"text":"Build It From Scratch proposed\nthat it was time for a whole new system."},{"time":538960,"text":"Separately, these two teams\nwere allowed to work full-time"},{"time":542759,"text":"on their particular approach."},{"time":544799,"text":"In engineering reviews,\nBill described his role as,"},{"time":547919,"text":"\"Injecting honesty into\nthe process by driving debate.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":552879,"text":"Early on, the teams were encouraged\nto build prototypes so that they could"},{"time":556879,"text":"\"bump them up against reality\nand discover for themselves"},{"time":560320,"text":"the strengths and weaknesses\nof their particular approach.\""},{"time":563120,"text":"When Build It From Scratch shared\ntheir prototype with the group"},{"time":566140,"text":"whose beepers would have\nto go off in the middle of the night"},{"time":569060,"text":"if something went wrong\nwith the website,"},{"time":571270,"text":"they heard loud and clear about the\nlimitations of their particular design."},{"time":576120,"text":"As the need for a solution\nbecame more urgent"},{"time":579039,"text":"and as the data, or the\nevidence, began to come in,"},{"time":582320,"text":"it became pretty clear\nthat the Big Table solution"},{"time":585600,"text":"was the right one for the moment."},{"time":588110,"text":"So they selected that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590200,"text":"But to make sure that\nthey did not lose the learning"},{"time":592960,"text":"of the Build it From Scratch team,"},{"time":594840,"text":"Bill asked two members of that team\nto join a new team that was emerging"},{"time":598250,"text":"to work on the next-generation system."},{"time":601240,"text":"This whole process took nearly two years,"},{"time":605000,"text":"but I was told that they were\nall working at breakneck speed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609399,"text":"Early in that process, one of the\nengineers had gone to Bill and said,"},{"time":612720,"text":"\"We're all too busy\nfor this inefficient system"},{"time":615759,"text":"of running parallel experiments.\""},{"time":618240,"text":"But as the process unfolded,\nhe began to understand"},{"time":621320,"text":"the wisdom of allowing talented\npeople to play out their passions."},{"time":625240,"text":"He admitted, \"If you had forced us\nto all be on one team,"},{"time":629039,"text":"we might have focused on proving\nwho was right, and winning,"},{"time":632480,"text":"and not on learning and discovering\nwhat was the best answer for Google.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":638000,"text":"Why is it that Pixar and Google\nare able to innovate time and again?"},{"time":641559,"text":"It's because they've mastered\nthe capabilities required for that."},{"time":645229,"text":"They know how to do\ncollaborative problem solving,"},{"time":647619,"text":"they know how to do\ndiscovery-driven learning"},{"time":649759,"text":"and they know how to do\nintegrated decision making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652460,"text":"Some of you may be sitting there\nand saying to yourselves right now,"},{"time":655679,"text":"\"We don't know how to do\nthose things in my organization."},{"time":658519,"text":"So why do they know how to\ndo those things at Pixar,"},{"time":661120,"text":"and why do they know how to\ndo those things at Google?\""},{"time":664559,"text":"When many of the people\nthat worked for Bill told us,"},{"time":667080,"text":"in their opinion, that Bill was one\nof the finest leaders in Silicon Valley,"},{"time":673480,"text":"we completely agreed;\nthe man is a genius."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677649,"text":"Leadership is the secret sauce."},{"time":680559,"text":"But it's a different kind of leadership,"},{"time":682960,"text":"not the kind many of us think about\nwhen we think about great leadership."},{"time":688290,"text":"One of the leaders I met with\nearly on said to me,"},{"time":690960,"text":"\"Linda, I don't read books on leadership."},{"time":694120,"text":"All they do is make me feel bad.\"\n(Laughter)"},{"time":697039,"text":"\"In the first chapter they say\nI'm supposed to create a vision."},{"time":700000,"text":"But if I'm trying to do something\nthat's truly new, I have no answers."},{"time":704240,"text":"I don't know what\ndirection we're going in"},{"time":706240,"text":"and I'm not even sure I know\nhow to figure out how to get there.\""},{"time":709899,"text":"For sure, there are times\nwhen visionary leadership"},{"time":712440,"text":"is exactly what is needed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714480,"text":"But if we want to build organizations\nthat can innovate time and again,"},{"time":717879,"text":"we must recast our understanding\nof what leadership is about."},{"time":722000,"text":"Leading innovation is about\ncreating the space"},{"time":725720,"text":"where people are willing\nand able to do the hard work"},{"time":728919,"text":"of innovative problem solving."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731399,"text":"At this point, some of you\nmay be wondering,"},{"time":735240,"text":"\"What does that leadership\nreally look like?\""},{"time":737559,"text":"At Pixar, they understand\nthat innovation takes a village."},{"time":742480,"text":"The leaders focus on building\na sense of community"},{"time":745919,"text":"and building those three capabilities."},{"time":748200,"text":"How do they define leadership?"},{"time":750480,"text":"They say leadership\nis about creating a world"},{"time":752759,"text":"to which people want to belong."},{"time":754720,"text":"What kind of world do people\nwant to belong in at Pixar?"},{"time":757360,"text":"A world where you're\nliving at the frontier."},{"time":759440,"text":"What do they focus their time on?"},{"time":761759,"text":"Not on creating a vision."},{"time":763230,"text":"Instead they spend\ntheir time thinking about,"},{"time":765360,"text":"\"How do we design a studio that has\nthe sensibility of a public square"},{"time":770200,"text":"so that people will interact?"},{"time":772360,"text":"Let's put in a policy that anyone,\nno matter what their level or role,"},{"time":776030,"text":"is allowed to give notes to the director"},{"time":777960,"text":"about how they feel\nabout a particular film."},{"time":780519,"text":"What can we do to make sure"},{"time":782519,"text":"that all the disruptors, all the\nminority voices in this organization,"},{"time":786399,"text":"speak up and are heard?"},{"time":788399,"text":"And, finally, let's bestow credit\nin a very generous way.\""},{"time":792020,"text":"I don't know if you've ever looked\nat the credits of a Pixar movie,"},{"time":795320,"text":"but the babies born during\na production are listed there."},{"time":798480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799879,"text":"How did Bill think about\nwhat his role was?"},{"time":802879,"text":"Bill said, \"I lead\na volunteer organization."},{"time":806360,"text":"Talented people don't want\nto follow me anywhere."},{"time":810120,"text":"They want to cocreate\nwith me the future."},{"time":813679,"text":"My job is to nurture the bottom-up"},{"time":816159,"text":"and not let it degenerate into chaos.\""},{"time":819519,"text":"How did he see his role?"},{"time":820840,"text":"\"I'm a role model,\nI'm a human glue,"},{"time":823639,"text":"I'm a connector,\nI'm an aggregator of viewpoints."},{"time":826279,"text":"I'm never a dictator of viewpoints.\""},{"time":828519,"text":"Advice about how you exercise the role?"},{"time":830639,"text":"Hire people who argue with you."},{"time":833139,"text":"And, guess what?"},{"time":834509,"text":"Sometimes it's best to be\ndeliberately fuzzy and vague."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839220,"text":"Some of you may\nbe wondering now,"},{"time":840969,"text":"what are these people thinking?"},{"time":842840,"text":"They're thinking,"},{"time":843850,"text":"\"I'm not the visionary,\nI'm the social architect."},{"time":846840,"text":"I'm creating the space where\npeople are willing and able"},{"time":850440,"text":"to share and combine\ntheir talents and passions.\""},{"time":853789,"text":"If some of you are worrying now\nthat you don't work at a Pixar,"},{"time":856919,"text":"or you don't work at a Google,"},{"time":858559,"text":"I want to tell you there's still hope."},{"time":861000,"text":"We've studied many organizations"},{"time":863000,"text":"that were really not\norganizations you'd think of"},{"time":865290,"text":"as ones where a lot of innovation happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":868220,"text":"We studied a general counsel\nin a pharmaceutical company"},{"time":871279,"text":"who had to figure out how\nto get the outside lawyers,"},{"time":874000,"text":"19 competitors,\nto collaborate and innovate."},{"time":876759,"text":"We studied the head of marketing\nat a German automaker"},{"time":880609,"text":"where, fundamentally, they believed\nthat it was the design engineers,"},{"time":883890,"text":"not the marketeers,\nwho were allowed to be innovative."},{"time":887009,"text":"We also studied Vineet Nayar\nat HCL Technologies,"},{"time":891120,"text":"an Indian outsourcing company."},{"time":893180,"text":"When we met Vineet,"},{"time":894729,"text":"his company was about, in his\nwords, to become irrelevant."},{"time":898080,"text":"We watched as he turned that company\ninto a global dynamo of I.T. innovation."},{"time":904600,"text":"At HCL technologies,\nlike at many companies,"},{"time":907560,"text":"the leaders had learned to see\ntheir role as setting direction"},{"time":911720,"text":"and making sure that\nno one deviated from it."},{"time":915139,"text":"What he did is tell them\nit was time for them"},{"time":919320,"text":"to think about rethinking\nwhat they were supposed to do."},{"time":922740,"text":"Because what was happening\nis that everybody was looking up"},{"time":925600,"text":"and you weren't seeing\nthe kind of bottom-up innovation"},{"time":928759,"text":"we saw at Pixar or Google."},{"time":931119,"text":"So they began to work on that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":932679,"text":"They stopped giving answers, they\nstopped trying to provide solutions."},{"time":936840,"text":"Instead, what they did\nis they began to see"},{"time":939679,"text":"the people at the bottom of the\npyramid, the young sparks,"},{"time":943556,"text":"the people who were\nclosest to the customers,"},{"time":946030,"text":"as the source of innovation."},{"time":948580,"text":"They began to transfer\nthe organization's growth"},{"time":951713,"text":"to that level."},{"time":955126,"text":"In Vineet's language, this was\nabout inverting the pyramid"},{"time":958879,"text":"so that you could unleash\nthe power of the many"},{"time":961919,"text":"by loosening the stranglehold of the few,"},{"time":964840,"text":"and increase the quality\nand the speed of innovation"},{"time":967960,"text":"that was happening every day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971600,"text":"For sure, Vineet and all the\nother leaders that we studied"},{"time":975389,"text":"were in fact visionaries."},{"time":978520,"text":"For sure, they understood\nthat that was not their role."},{"time":983060,"text":"So I don't think it is accidental\nthat many of you did not recognize Ed."},{"time":988240,"text":"Because Ed, like Vineet, understands\nthat our role as leaders"},{"time":992919,"text":"is to set the stage, not perform on it."},{"time":997080,"text":"If we want to invent a better future,"},{"time":999960,"text":"and I suspect that's why\nmany of us are here,"},{"time":1003240,"text":"then we need to reimagine our task."},{"time":1007120,"text":"Our task is to create the space"},{"time":1009799,"text":"where everybody's slices of genius"},{"time":1012440,"text":"can be unleashed and harnessed,"},{"time":1016960,"text":"and turned into works\nof collective genius."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019720,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1021790,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}